Rooms:
Foyer
Contents: Beretta,combatDagger,typewriter,inkRibbon
You find yourself in a large entrance hall, which is quite drafty. A red carpet
in the middle leads to a split staircase. White columns and arches line the
walls, supporting the upper level. To the left side of the staircase, on a
small round table, sits an old typewriter.
---
Dining Room
Contents: woodenEmblem
A long, rectangular table with rounded corners spans almost the entire length
of the room. A grandfather clock, leaning against the north wall, ticks loudly.
At the far west end, a wooden emblem with a gold crest hangs above the
fireplace.
---
Art Showroom
Contents: firstFloorMap
It's dark in here, except for several spotlights which illuminate the various
paintings covering the walls. A statue, depicting a woman carrying an urn on
her shoulder, stands in the center. There's also a red curtain in the corner.
---
2F
Contents: lockpick
On the way up, you pass an ornate work of stained glass on the wall above the
landing. Reaching the top of the stairs, you notice the nearby walkway over-
looking the massive foyer below —— an impressive view, to be sure.
---
Hallway
Although nothing catches your eye, you hear distant sounds of flesh being torn
from bone...
---
Sitting Area
Contents: zombie
A corner sectional is the only piece of furniture in sight in this little nook,
but more importantly ——
A shadowy figure is crouched over something, and it appears not to notice you.
You should probably leave while you still can...!
---
Bar
Contents: musicalScore,grandPiano,bookshelf
Wow, this place is fancy! Everything, from the stools to the hardwood flooring,
boasts of an owner who has money to burn. Bottles of all shapes and sizes fill
the shelves behind the counter. A beautiful grand piano occupies one corner of
the room. It looks like it hasn't been played in a while, yet has remained in
surprisingly pristine condition.
---
Secret Passage
Contents: wolfMedal
Until you came along, this particular area had long been abandoned. A gentle
breeze blows through the bars of the intimidating wrought iron gate that's
blocking the path north.
---
Winding Corridor
Weaving its way westward, a serpentine hallway passes by many other rooms.
---
Marble Room
A feeling of claustrophobia washes over you while you contemplate the purpose
of this boxlike space made of polished stone. The ceiling's unusually low
height doesn't help, either...
---
Living Room
Contents: shotgun
The furniture here includes a fireplace, coffee table, and leather sofa (how
cozy!). The floor is covered with a decorative rug. A well-crafted shotgun
hangs on two metal hooks attached to the back wall.
---
Back Passage
This is a narrow passage leading further into the mansion. It is meant for
private use, probably by the owner, their close friends, or special guests.
---
Study
Contents: Necronomicon
Considering how frustrating it was to get here, you wonder who could have
possibly used this room. An ominous book with a pentagram on its cover lies on
a small mahogany desk.
---
Courtyard
Contents: firstAidSpray
A gorgeous fountain commands your attention upon entering. Oddly enough, the
water has been drained from it. Peering inside the fountain, your eyes follow a
series of stone steps leading down to two imposing steel doors. On the wall
beside them is carved a circular indentation.
---
Underground Lab Entrance
Contents: securityGuard
Startled by your sudden presence, a sleepy security guard fumbles for his gun.
While he's distracted, you spot a set of doors behind him with yet
another circular indentation.
---
Underground Lab
Contents: rocketLauncher,Tyrant
You're surrounded by strange, humming machines, near each of which a computer
monitor flickers eerily. Multiple disfigured specimens float in large, murky
test tubes. Broken glass is scattered before one shattered cryotube. Be
careful, for a dangerous enemy lurks within...
---
Emergency Tunnel
Contents: battery
A cacophony of blaring sirens as well as the hissing steam from some burst
pipes assault your senses. Squinting hard while covering your ears to protect
them from the din, you barely detect the faint outline of an elevator at the
other end of the tunnel. When you finally reach the elevator through the dense
mist, however, you realize it has run out of power. Oh no! Luckily, someone
was kind enough to leave a battery behind. What a relief!
---
Helipad
Contents: signalFlare
Dawn breaks as you emerge from the elevator onto the platform attached to the
mansion's rooftop. Find a way to contact your teammate, or else you'll be
engulfed in flames!
---
